    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Never published before this edition.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Ἀστυ-"><seg part="I">Ἀστυ</seg><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="2" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName></persName>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Asty<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">fils de</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Asty<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">son of</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Asty<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">figlio di</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p/>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
             <p>Several personal names with first stem <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀστυ-</foreign> being known in Cyrenaica, no further restoration is possible here. As there was space only for two lines on the stone, the tiny vestiges 
             of two letters at line 2 should belong to the father's name. The block was cut for being inserted into a monument, probably honorific, of which it would have been a sort of lintel.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
